name: Christian McCaffrey
summary: Christian McCaffrey, running back for the San Francisco 49ers, sustained a serious knee injury during a game against the Buffalo Bills, potentially ending his season. The injury is believed to be a PCL injury, and coach Kyle Shanahan has indicated that McCaffrey could miss the rest of the 2024 season. McCaffrey was injured in the second quarter and was downgraded to out for the remainder of the game. The injury occurred during a run where McCaffrey bulldozed through a Bills defender. The 49ers' medical staff is providing discouraging news on McCaffrey's condition, casting doubt on his availability for the rest of the season.
